        "commenting"
      ],
      "body": {
        "type": "TextualBody",
        "value": "The shadow-mirror-creature is now seen walking off beyond the corner, just like the silhouette of the man was at the beginning of the film. This then signals the start of the cyclical nature of the film. This is also important for us to remember when connecting the idea of the woman's shadow and the man at the end of the story. This is the largest part in the film that pushes me to believe that both shadows are created or affected by the man. ",
        "format": "text/plain",
        "purpose": "commenting"
      },
